# OpenWeed MVP - Environment Variables for Deployment

This file contains only the essential environment variables needed for deployment.
Additional variables are automatically managed through Vercel Marketplace integrations.

## Required for Deployment

```env
# Database (Required)
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://username:password@host:port/database"

# Authentication (Required)
NEXTAUTH_URL="https://your-domain.vercel.app"
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-secret-key-here"

# Email Configuration (Required)
EMAIL_SERVER_HOST="smtp.gmail.com"
EMAIL_SERVER_PORT=587
EMAIL_SERVER_USER="your-email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_SERVER_PASSWORD="your-app-password"
EMAIL_FROM="noreply@openweed.co"

# File Upload (Required)
UPLOADTHING_SECRET="your-uploadthing-secret"
UPLOADTHING_APP_ID="your-uploadthing-app-id"

# Environment
NODE_ENV="production"
```

## Optional Services (Auto-configured via Vercel Integrations)

The following services are automatically configured when you connect them via Vercel Marketplace:

- **Mapbox**: Connect via Vercel Marketplace → Mapbox integration
- **Supabase**: Connect via Vercel Marketplace → Supabase integration
- **Additional services**: Available through Vercel's growing marketplace

## Deployment Setup

1. **Connect Vercel Integrations**
   - Go to your Vercel project dashboard
   - Navigate to "Integrations" tab
   - Connect required services (Database, Email, File Upload)
   - Optional services will be auto-configured

2. **Environment Variables**
   - Add the required variables above to your Vercel project
   - Vercel will automatically inject integration variables

3. **Deploy**
   ```bash
   vercel --prod
   ```

